{
  "texts": [
    "Salton et al.",
    "introduced a non-binary weight model called the 𝑣𝑒𝑐𝑡𝑜𝑟 𝑠𝑝𝑎𝑐𝑒 𝑚𝑜𝑑𝑒𝑙 (VSM) [33] to rank the relevant documents based on search queries.",
    "The VSM [33] transforms text processing into vector computation in vector space, presents semantic similarity through spatial similarity, and thus compensates for the Boolean model's inability to scale the returned documents.",
    "However, approaches based on the VSM model fail to recognize semantic ambiguity in the text due to their dependence on token frequency, and cannot solve the problems of polysemy and synonymy.The BM25 probabilistic model [115] is among the best weighting models for IR [16, 27, 54-56, 59, 60, 95, 135, 140].",
    "It assigns a weight to a search term based on its intra-document term frequency and query term frequency."
  ]
}